soviet defense spending rose 3 percent last year, despite president mikhail s. gorbachev's promises cut military budget, according intelligence report released sunday.
study, prepared jointly cia pentagon's defense intelligence agency, also said gorbachev laying groundwork proposed 14.2 percent cut defense spending.
study said chopping military spending sharply would require soviets reduce armed forces 500,000-troop reduction announced gorbachev last december, meaning cutbacks soviet military.
newly declassified report painted grim overall picture soviet economy.
said gorbachev forced slow pace economic reforms delay key steps allowing market set wholesale retail prices.
reforms good chance success long run, likely cause gorbachev short term political problems consumers want see faster improvement bureaucrats resent loss power economic decision-making, report said.
economy hampered sluggish industrial agricultural performance, disruptions confusion stemming gorbachev's reforms, cost coping earthquake struck armenia last december, report said.
``according estimates, soviet economy grew 1.5 percent 1988 _ second straight poor yearly showing,'' study said.
cost rebuilding armenia exceed estimated $11.2 billion price tag cleaning 1986 chernobyl nuclear reactor disaster, cia predicted.
factors contributed budget deficit cia estimated 9 percent soviet gross national product, value goods services produced economy.
last year kremlin admitted first time running deficit, although estimates amount varied among soviet economists.
poor economic performance forced gorbachev back away programs, need provide consumer goods impelling decrease defense spending, report said.
``soviet media indicated campaigns modernize industrial plant equipment reform economic system even much-vaunted anti-alcohol campaign failing occasioning major disruptions,'' said.
``gorbachev remains committed original vision revitalized economy,'' report said.
``he has, however, apparently concluded cannot realize vision rapidly thought possible, proceed directly along path initially planned follow.''
``the shifts gorbachev implemented, view, potential, sustained, boost consumer welfare bring sense order economy,'' report said.
``gorbachev acknowledged consumer welfare must substantially improved soon regime develop broad-based popular support perestroika,'' reforms called russian, said.
mean 14.2 percent cut defense spending, gorbachev announced january, first time put firm number cuts discussed part new military doctrine known ``reasonable sufficiency.''
despite proclamation new ``defensive'' military doctrine past two years, ``soviet defense spending, measured constant 1982 rubles, grew roughly 3 percent, line growth rates past several years,'' cia said.
``procurement weapons systems major contributor growth,'' cia said.
``missile procurement _ particularly icbms (intercontinental ballistic missiles) strategic surface-to-air missiles _ also displayed growth.''
``last year, however, gorbachev took several actions evidently intended lay groundwork future military cuts,'' report said.
key points gorbachev's plan cut military spending ``remain unclear,'' report said, may involve substantially larger cuts 500,000 troop reduction announced last december.
``indeed, estimates indicate reduce total defense budget 14.2 percent, soviets would go beyond cutbacks military programs specifically promised make.''
